Social Media Do’s & Don’ts -: 
Do’s –
•	Think before you post anything 
•	Try to be polite while talking online 
•	Keep your personal info safe 
•	Share useful or positive things 
•	Check if something is true or not before sharing
 
Don’ts –
•	Don’t post anything rude or hurting others 
•	Don’t share personal details openly 
•	Don’t argue for no reason in comments 
•	Don’t share too much about your life 
•	Don’t spread fake news without checking
PART – B Real-Life Scenario - 
Sometimes poor digital communication can create problems without us even realising it. For example, if a student send a message or email to a professor in hurry, it may not sound right. Even if the student didn’t mean to be rude, the message can look disrespectful or confusing. Because of this, the professor might misunderstand and not respond properly, which can affect the student work also.
This kind of situation can be avoided if the student just take some time before sending the message. Writing in a simple and polite way, and checking it once, can really help. Small things like using proper greeting and respectful words makes a difference. Good communication is important because it avoids confusion and helps in maintaining a good impression in front of others.


